        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 4:57AM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 456 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ridgeview, or 18 miles northeast of Eagle Butte, moving northeast at
55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eagle Butte, Timber Lake, Swiftbird, White Horse, Green Grass, Little
Moreau Rec Area, Trail City, Laplant, Parade, Blackfoot, Ridgeview,
Tiospaye Topa School, Spring Lake, Promise, Swiftbird Day School,
Grand River Casino, Glencross, Indian Memorial Rec Area, Cheyenne
River Reservation, and Lake Oahe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Aberdeen.</instruction>
